@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<section class="hero-panel">
    <span class="eyebrow">Week 8 Project 04</span>
    <h1>Partial page updates with HTMX and Razor Pages.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        HTMX lets you add CRUD interactions to any HTML element using attributes like
        <code>hx-get</code>, <code>hx-post</code>, <code>hx-target</code>, and <code>hx-swap</code>
        — without writing JavaScript.
    </p>
    <div class="action-row">
        <a class="button button-primary" asp-page="/HtmxLab">Open HTMX Lab</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="https://htmx.org/docs/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">HTMX Docs</a>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Learning Objectives</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Use <code>hx-get</code> and <code>hx-post</code> to make HTTP requests from HTML elements.</li>
            <li>Use <code>hx-target</code> and <code>hx-swap</code> to control where responses appear.</li>
            <li>Build a full CRUD table (Create, Read, Update, Delete) with inline editing.</li>
            <li>Return partial views from Razor Pages handler methods.</li>
            <li>Display loading indicators with <code>hx-indicator</code>.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Key HTMX Attributes</h2>
        <ul>
            @foreach (var attr in Model.HtmxAttributes)
            {
                <li><code>@attr.Name</code> — @attr.Description</li>
            }
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>

<section class="info-panel">
    <h2>Suggested classroom walkthrough</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Open the HTMX Lab and add a new student using the form at the bottom.</li>
        <li>Inspect the Network tab in DevTools — notice only the table fragment is returned, not the full page.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Edit</strong> on a row and modify a field, then confirm the row swaps inline.</li>
        <li>Delete a student and observe the row removal with <code>hx-swap="outerHTML"</code>.</li>
        <li>Discuss: when is HTMX a better choice than Alpine.js or a full SPA framework?</li>
    </ol>
</section>
